Package org.forgerock.openam.entitlement.rest.wrappers

Class ApplicationWrapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.forgerock.openam.entitlement.rest.wrappers.ApplicationWrapper
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<ApplicationWrapper>
    public class ApplicationWrapper
extends Object
implements Comparable<ApplicationWrapper>
    Wrapper for the Jsonification of the Application class. Taking an instance of an Application this class exposes the necessary parts of that class to the Jackson ObjectMapper via annotations. You cannot set the complex object ApplicationType in a single simple operation as it requires verification of the subject's ability to access the referenced ApplicationType. As such, a second call to this wrapper must be made after the initial parsing of the JSON to populate the ApplicationType having first determined the Subject which is requesting this operation.

        public boolean setApplicationType​(Subject mySubject,
                                  String applicationTypeName)
        Retrieves the ApplicationType specified by the request, ensuring that the Subject supplied has the authorization. Returns true if the ApplicationType was set successfully, false otherwise.
        Parameters:
        mySubject - The user's Subject
        applicationTypeName - The ApplicationType name to look up - the returning ApplicationType will be used
        Returns:
        True if we set an ApplicationType on this Application
